<div class="mdui-typo"><h1 id="entertainment-n">entertainment <strong><em>n</em></strong></h1>
<p>英 /ˌentə'teɪnmənt/    美 /ˌentər'teɪnmənt/  </p>
<h2 id="_1">释义</h2>
<h4 id="1">1.★ <strong>娱乐；娱乐节目 / 活动：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p><strong>the entertainment business / world</strong>
娱乐业/界</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>I think watching TV is not just for entertainment.
我认为看电视不仅仅为了娱乐。</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>This season's entertainments include five new plays and several concerts.
这一季的娱乐活动包括五场戏剧和几场音乐会。</p></div>

<h4 id="2u">2.<strong>[U] 招待；款待：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>She was busy with the entertainment of the guests.
她正忙着招待客人。</p></div></div>